section.section:
Beginning in fiscal year 2006 and annually thereafter, to maintain the rate increases provided under this paragraph, disbursements from the Medical Assistance Program Account of $15,000,000 shall be used by the Secretary to increase fee-for-service health care provider rates and to pay managed care organization health care providers consistent with fee-for-service health care provider rates for procedures commonly performed by:
obstetricians;
neurosurgeons;
orthopedic surgeons; and
emergency medicine physicians.

Portions of the Medical Assistance Program Account that exceed the amount provided under paragraph (2) of this subsection shall be used by the Secretary only to:
increase capitation payments to managed care organizations consistent with § 15-103(b)(18) of the Health - General Article;
increase fee-for-service health care provider rates;
pay managed care organization health care providers consistent with the fee-for-service health care provider rates; and
after fiscal year 2008:
maintain increased capitation payments to managed care organizations;
maintain increased rates for health care providers;
in accordance with § 6-121(b)(3) of this article, support the provision of office-based specialty care, diagnostic testing, and laboratory tests for individuals with family income that does not exceed 200% of the federal poverty level; and
support generally the operations of the Maryland Medical Assistance Program.
